---

<Layout title="The Creator Design Kit - Approachable Design" description="Learn design fundamentals and build a design kit that scales. A 20-day email course for non-designers." ogImage="/images/products/creator-design-kit-social.png" stickyHeader={false}>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="md:flex md:items-center md:gap-12 lg:gap-16">
        <!-- Left: Text Content -->
        <div class="md:w-1/2 lg:w-3/5">
          <span class="inline-block bg-white/10 text-white/80 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider px-4 py-2 rounded-full mb-6">
            A Design Course for Creators
          </span>
          <h1 class="text-balance font-display-black-italic text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl mb-6">
            Design Like a Pro in 20 Days
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/60 mb-6 max-w-xl">
            Stop second-guessing every font, color, and layout. Learn the 80/20 of design that lets you create professional visuals—without hiring a designer or spending years learning.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-white mb-8">
            Course starts Monday. You're 20 days away from design confidence.
          </p>
          <a href="#pricing" class="btn btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-4 gap-2">
            Start Designing with Confidence
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10.293 3.293a1 1 0 011.414 0l6 6a1 1 0 010 1.414l-6 6a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L14.586 11H3a1 1 0 110-2h11.586l-4.293-4.293a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </a>

          <!-- Social Proof -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 mt-10 text-sm">
            <span class="text-brand-coral font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider">Join 250+ Students</span>
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-white/60">
              <span class="text-yellow-400">⚡</span>
              Highlighted by:
              <span class="font-semibold text-white">Trends.vc</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Product Image with Glow -->
        <div class="md:w-1/2 lg:w-2/5 mt-12 md:mt-0 relative">
          <!-- Atmospheric glow -->
          <div class="hero-glow"></div>
          <img
            src="/images/site/creator-design-kit.png"
            alt="The Creator Design Kit"
            class="w-full max-w-[336px] mx-auto relative z-10"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hero Testimonials -->
  <div class="py-8">
    <TestimonialScroll rows={heroTestimonials} />
  </div>

  <!-- Design Decisions Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-brand-coral text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Updated {lastUpdated}</p>
        <h2 class="font-display-black-italic text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl mb-6">
          Even if you're not a designer, you're still making design decisions.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-8">
          Have you ever spent money on design, and realized you just made a huge mistake?
        </p>

        <!-- GIF -->
        <div class="mb-8 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <img src="/images/products/huge-mistake.gif" alt="I've made a huge mistake" class="w-full" />
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          It didn't turn out, and you don't know how to fix it. So you hired a different designer and it was even worse!
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-8">
          It's a sick cycle, because you don't trust yourself to make these decisions yourself.
        </p>

        <!-- Pain Quantification -->
        <div class="bg-brand-dark-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/10 mb-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-white/80 mb-4">The cost of not knowing design:</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-white/70">
            <p>$500-2,000 for a designer who doesn't get your vision</p>
            <p>+ 10+ hours of back-and-forth revisions</p>
            <p>+ Another $500-1,000 when you try a different designer</p>
            <p>+ Endless hours second-guessing every visual decision</p>
            <p class="pt-2 border-t border-white/10 text-white font-semibold">= $1,000-3,000+ and weeks of frustration</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-brand-coral mt-4 font-medium">Or you could learn the fundamentals yourself in 20 days.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          In this course, I'll help you understand not only how to make better design decisions, but also how to avoid them.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-8">
          Author Paul Millerd turned his podcast art from amateur to pro just by learning how to use color, typography, and eye-catching layouts without the help of a designer.
        </p>

        <!-- Before/After -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <img src="/images/products/paul-millerd-before-after.avif" alt="Paul Millerd's podcast art - Before and After" class="w-full rounded-xl" />
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          Imagine having the ability to make your own design decisions, or to give design feedback to a designer.
        </p>

        <p class="text-xl text-white font-semibold mb-4">Decisions like:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8 text-xl text-white/70">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-white/50">•</span>
            <span>Learn to choose and combine colors that don't clash</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-white/50">•</span>
            <span>Why you should never use pure black</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-white/50">•</span>
            <span>How to choose an indestructible font family</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-white/50">•</span>
            <span>How to use spacing and grids for beautiful layouts</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-white/50">•</span>
            <span>How to design yourself in Figma!</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">And so much more!</p>

        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          If you have ever worked with a designer but you're never happy with the results, there's a design gap. Not all designers are created equal, and if you can't communicate your visual ideas, it's going to be difficult to hit the mark consistently.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          This course will take you through the steps to building out a design kit at the end, giving you a shortcut to working with designers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/70 mb-6">
          You don't need to be a designer to make some damn good design decisions. You just need the 80/20.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-white font-semibold">
          This email course will show you how.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

